metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #177
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Deep Thoughts #106
metadata.description:
There are times when we think about something, we just go deeper and deeper, and soon we find ourselves in a position that we can't stop thinking about it.

While sometimes this may be enjoyable or even good for us, we should also never forget that, some depths have no coming back.

* * *

metadata.name: Mythic Latent Glitches  #198
metadata.description:
What is even real and what is artificial?

In the contemporary light, the division between real and artificial loses weight as the concepts become more and more intertwined. In this work, the artist combines the human and generative inputs, in a counterintuitive manner, by allowing AI to design the organic elements and using the human hand to incorporate artificial glitches. What seemingly emerges as natural forms, was imagined solely by GAN, seeing the world through the limited examples through the photographer‚Äôs lenses. Artist‚Äôs role is also reversed, as their goal is to design the visual destruction process of the organic forms. Glitch is a malfunction of perception, it symbolizes the confusion caused by not being able to comprehend. 

The human fascination with metaphysical forces spans many centuries. While Pagan mythology created gods living in deep forests and under-explored territories, nowadays we approach technology with somewhat similar awe, fascination, and fear. 

The project has been developed in multiple stages. It started with an inspiration by the Lithuanian landscape and research of the ancient myths and legends. The photography aimed at capturing the mysterious, spanning months and years of different experiences. A custom pre-trained artist‚Äôs GAN model was then trained on a collection of several hundred photographs in high resolution. Selected outputs were curated by artist and included as a starting canvas for the next stage. Then, a set of stochastic manipulations were programmed to create alternative narratives through the visual destruction. Fog turns into smoke into burning radioactive forest in an unpredictable manner, guided by the random variables, their boundaries crafted by artist.  

Read more on the project website:
ivonatau.com/mythic-latent-glitches

- Use the "A" key to animate (if "Animated" feature is present).
- Press any key to stop the animation.
- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: Dencity #731
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ‚ù§Ô∏è, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Plottable Circleception (8 frames) #36
metadata.description:
**Collection on https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/greweb**

'Circleception' explores fractal-like zoom loops (the art infinitely reproduces inside itself), packing circles, filled with various techniques.

A SVG file can be exported (right-click save) to plot the 8 frames of this animation on a A4 paper. This is a "plot loop". The physical piece is displayed as aesthetics 4x2 grid of the frames. The animation is meant to be run at 16 FPS speed.

You can enjoy the digital version that simulates ink effects. But also, thanks to the utility token decoupling, get a physical one: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their materials and ship to collectors ‚Äì as long as NFT is owned at request time.

Example: https://greweb.me/plots/543

@greweb ‚Äì 2022 ‚Äì tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM ‚Äì CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Chaosplot #81
metadata.description:
Continued exploration of the algorithm from "Chaospill" with a symmetric two tone style that is plotter friendly. The result can be rotated to whatever orientation works best for your display purposes. The code is presented unminified with comments and will be open sourced soon.

Live Mode Controls

Click to regenerate with a different starting seed.
1 - Save a SVG, the result is sized for 11"x17" prints with each color on a separate layer
2 - Save a PNG of the output
3 - Switch paper size to 8.5"x11" letter or A1 for different size plots
4 - Toggle HD mode which increases resolution and disables noise for printing

Code and Outputs are Copyright (C) 2022 Frank Force - Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0.
